# Security

## Network

- Bind API to `127.0.0.1` only — never `0.0.0.0` in default config
- No outbound telemetry in OSS core
- CORS: localhost origins only

## Data handling

- User memory may contain secrets (URLs, keys, internal names) — treat as confidential
- Never log `MemoryRecord.content` at info level
- Error responses must not echo file contents
- Tests use synthetic fixtures only

## Writes

- All mutations through WriteGuard
- Backup before every write
- Refuse Cursor SQLite writes when Cursor process detected (best-effort)
- Validate paths stay within allowed roots (no `../` escape)

## Dependencies

- Run `pnpm audit` before release; fix high/critical or document exception
